# Studio agent rules

Read these docs before changing `studio/`, `packs/*`, or `topis/tasks/`:

1. `docs/studio/README.md`
2. `docs/studio/architecture.md`
3. `docs/studio/rules.md`

Core constraints:

- `studio/` is project-agnostic kernel code. Keep my-ft domain facts in
  `topis/football-docs/`, `topis/tasks/`, or `packs/my-ft/`.
- Run planning before execution. `topis/tasks/*.yaml` normally should not set
  `goal`; `goal` is derived by planner/fallback unless explicitly overridden.
- Roles cannot write files. Card writes must go through `CardRunner -> gates ->
  atomic_write`.
- Skills use markdown + YAML front-matter. Generic skills go in
  `studio/skills_builtin/`; project skills go in `packs/<pack>/skills/`.
- Context changes must define role visibility, trim policy, and tests.
- Memory is append-only jsonl with deterministic digest; do not summarize memory
  with an LLM.
- Provider/model differences belong in `studio/llm/providers/` or
  `studio/llm/models/`; do not hard-code provider behavior in `LLMClient`.
- Runtime status output must go through `RunLogger`; preserve checkpoint writes
  to `work/runs/<run_id>/plan.json`.
- Terminal rendering must live in `studio/printing/`; keep Rich styles out of
  business logic and logger file-writing code.
- LLM token streaming must use provider `on_delta` callbacks and
  `RunLogger.message_delta`; providers must never print directly.

Required validation after kernel changes:

```bash
python3 -m pytest
python3 -m studio.cli validate --pack packs/my-ft
python3 -m studio.cli skills --pack packs/my-ft
python3 -m studio.cli run --pack packs/my-ft --task topis/tasks/01-foundation.yaml --dry-run
```
